\section{Posterior summary choices}{

The \code{beta_summary} argument controls which posterior summary statistic is
used as the point-estimate beta weight:
\describe{
\item{\code{"mean"}}{Posterior mean. Minimum MSE estimator; default and
recommended for most use cases.}
\item{\code{"median"}}{Posterior median. More robust when horseshoe priors
produce heavy-tailed marginals for near-zero coefficients.}
\item{\code{"Q2.5"} / \code{"Q97.5"}}{Credible interval bounds. Useful for
sensitivity analysis (e.g. conservative lower-bound weighting).}
}
